  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with significant legal consequences. Potential legal ramifications typically include:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial fines\n- Prison sentences (often several years)\n- Federal and state level criminal charges\n\n2. Civil Penalties\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Financial institution sanctions\n- Monetary penalties\n\n3. Professional Consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential career restrictions\n- Professional reputation damage\n\n4. International Legal Actions\n- Potential extradition\n- International financial sanctions\n- Cross-border legal proceedings\n\n5. Additional Charges\n- Potential associated charges like:\n- Tax evasion\n- Fraud\n- Conspiracy\n\nSpecific penalties vary based on jurisdiction, amount involved, and specific circumstances of the case.",
